Why AGPL for the portal and the joins registry?

The interactive query builder (portal/src/pages/transformar.astro),
the dataset-graph (portal/src/pages/conexoes.astro), and the curated
join registry (catalog/joins.yaml) together encode domain knowledge
about how Brazilian audiovisual datasets connect. They are the
sensitive parts of this project.

AGPL-3.0 ensures that if anyone runs a modified version of this
software as a network-accessible service (SaaS, internal portal,
embedded product), they must publish their modified source under
the same license. This protects the open-source nature of the work
against private commercial appropriation.

The rest of the repository (pipelines, cleaned data) uses more
permissive licenses — see the root README for the full breakdown.
